<subSubSection id="1CBB6542FFCFFF5425CAF979FBAEFA75" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="549" pageId="1" pageNumber="548" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCFFF5725CAF979FE21F8A6" blockId="1.[151,1437,1625,1976]" pageId="1" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCFFF5725CAF979FEB7F951" bold="true" box="[199,314,1733,1759]" pageId="1" pageNumber="548">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(from 
<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFCFFF57248AF97AFD42F96E" author="Bousfield, E. L. &amp; Hendrycks, E. A." box="[391,719,1734,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="548" pagination="17 - 57" refId="ref6232" refString="Bousfield, E. L. &amp; Hendrycks, E. A. (1994) A revision of family Pleustidae (Amphipoda: Gammaridea). Part 1. Systematics and biogeography of component subfamilies. Amphipacifica, 1 (1), 17 - 57." type="journal article" year="1994">Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks 1994</bibRefCitation>
with additions). Body smooth. Rostrum short. Lateral head lobe rounded. Eyes rounded or reniform. Antenna 1, peduncle 1 without antero-distal process. Antenna 2, peduncular segments 4 and 5 setose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCFFF5725CAF88EFDE6F836" blockId="1.[151,1437,1625,1976]" pageId="1" pageNumber="548">Mandible, row of raker setae short, with 4–7 pectinate blades; left lacinia 6–7-dentate; right lacinia blade-like. Maxilla 1, inner plate with two stout plumose apical setae. Maxilla 2, inner plate with two strong submarginal setae. Maxilliped, inner plate with 2–4 apical button spine-like setae; palp segment 3 not produced distally, broadened, dactylus slender, curved, micro-pectinate.</paragraph>
<caption id="00DE6641FFCCFF54259AFB8FFE52FB1D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457370" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6457370" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457370/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" startId="2.[151,250,1075,1099]" targetBox="[156,1431,186,1046]" targetPageId="2">
