<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFCCFF542055FBEBFF47FB1D" author="Labay, V. S." pageId="2" pageNumber="549" pagination="220 - 230" refId="ref6589" refString="Labay, V. S. (2018) Cognateosymtes serraticoxae, new genus, new species, a pleustid amphipod from the Sea of Japan (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Gammaridea: Pleustidae: Eosymtinae). Zootax a, 4521 (2), 220 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4521.2.4" type="journal article" year="2018">Labay, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFCCFF54241DFBC7FE00FB1D" author="Labay, V. S." box="[272,397,1147,1171]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" pagination="220 - 230" refId="ref6589" refString="Labay, V. S. (2018) Cognateosymtes serraticoxae, new genus, new species, a pleustid amphipod from the Sea of Japan (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Gammaridea: Pleustidae: Eosymtinae). Zootax a, 4521 (2), 220 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4521.2.4" type="journal article" year="2018">Labay 2018</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2a)
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCCFF5425CAFB7DFF7BFB71" blockId="2.[151,1437,1217,1856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Coxal plates 1–4 medium, increasing posteriorly; posterodistally with one small cusp. Coxal gills medium, sac-like.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCCFF5425CAFAB5FCE6FAC9" blockId="2.[151,1437,1217,1856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Pereopods 1 &amp; 2 (gnathopods 1 &amp; 2) medium, subsimilar; carpus shorter than propodus, posterodistal lobe shallow; palmar margin of propodus oblique, without medium tooth.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCCFF5425CAFAEDFC6DFA1E" blockId="2.[151,1437,1217,1856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Pereopods 3–7 slender, medium long, dactylus elongate. Pereopods 5–7, coxae shallow, lobes rounded; bases broadly rounded behind, increasing in size posteriorly, hind margin serrate.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCCFF5425CAFA25FD81FA56" blockId="2.[151,1437,1217,1856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Epimeral plates 1–3, posterior corners acuminate, not produced. Uropod 3 slender, outer ramus not more than 2/3 the length of the inner ramus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCCFF5425CAFA5DFBAEFA75" blockId="2.[151,1437,1217,1856]" box="[199,1059,1505,1532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Telson linguiform, apex subtruncate or rounded, incised; with proximal keel.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CBB6542FFCCFF5425CAF9B9FC87F95D" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCCFF5425CAF9B9FE20F9CD" blockId="2.[151,1437,1217,1856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF5425CAF9B9FEECF991" bold="true" box="[199,353,1541,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Distribution.</emphasis>
Marine waters of boreal part of Pacific Ocean (
<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFCCFF542666F9B9FB38F991" author="Bousfield, E. L. &amp; Hendrycks, E. A." box="[875,1205,1541,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" pagination="17 - 57" refId="ref6232" refString="Bousfield, E. L. &amp; Hendrycks, E. A. (1994) A revision of family Pleustidae (Amphipoda: Gammaridea). Part 1. Systematics and biogeography of component subfamilies. Amphipacifica, 1 (1), 17 - 57." type="journal article" year="1994">Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFCCFF5421B2F9B9FE80F9CD" author="Hendrycks, E. A. &amp; Bousfield, E. L." pageId="2" pageNumber="549" pagination="45 - 113" refId="ref6534" refString="Hendrycks, E. A. &amp; Bousfield, E. L. (2004) The amphipod family Pleustidae (mainly subfamilies Mesopleustinae, Neopleustinae, Pleusymtinae and Stenopleustinae) from the Pacific coast of North America: systematics and distributional ecology. Amphipacifica, 3 (4), 45 - 113." type="journal article" year="2004">Hendrycks &amp; Bousfield 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFCCFF542415F995FE2CF9CD" author="Labay, V. S." box="[280,417,1577,1603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" pagination="220 - 230" refId="ref6589" refString="Labay, V. S. (2018) Cognateosymtes serraticoxae, new genus, new species, a pleustid amphipod from the Sea of Japan (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Gammaridea: Pleustidae: Eosymtinae). Zootax a, 4521 (2), 220 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4521.2.4" type="journal article" year="2018">Labay 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCCFF5425CAF9F1FC87F95D" blockId="2.[151,1437,1217,1856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF5425CAF9F1FEFDF9E9" bold="true" box="[199,368,1613,1639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Relationships.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="93A14D4AFFCCFF54247AF9F2FE6CF9E9" authorityName="Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks" authorityYear="1994" box="[375,481,1614,1639]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pleustidae" genus="Eosymtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF54247AF9F2FE6CF9E9" box="[375,481,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Eosymtes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="93A14D4AFFCCFF54277BF9F2FCA3F9E6" authorityName="Labay" authorityYear="2018" box="[630,814,1614,1640]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pleustidae" genus="Cognateosymtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF54277BF9F2FCA3F9E6" box="[630,814,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Cognateosymtes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of character states (
<figureCitation id="CC9A2A4CFFCCFF542069F9F1FF28F905" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1075,1099]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,186,1046]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[151,1436,181,1051]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Eosymtinae Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks, 1994, lateral view: a—Eosymtes minutus Bousfield and Hendrycks, 1994 (from Bousfield and Hendrycks 1994: fig. 7), b—Eosymtes magnumoculis sp. nov., c—Cognateosymtes serraticoxae Labay, 2018 (from Labay 2018: fig. 2a)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457370" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457370/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CC9A2A4CFFCCFF5425B9F9CDFF48F905" box="[180,197,1649,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,201,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-16@3.[151,1436,181,1774]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Eosymtinae Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks, 1994: a–c—peduncle of antenna 1; d–f—maxilla 2; g–i—palp of maxilliped; j–l—coxal plates 1–3 posteroventrally; m, n, o—propodus and dactylus of pereopods 3–7; a, d, g, j, m—Eosymtes minutus Bousfield and Hendrycks, 1994 (from Bousfield and Hendrycks 1994), b, e, h, k, n—Eosymtes magnumoculis sp. nov., c, f, i, l, o—Cognateosymtes serraticoxae Labay, 2018 (from Labay 2018)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457374" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457374/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">2</figureCitation>
): antenna 1, peduncular segment 1 without strong anterodistal processes; coxae 1–3, posterodistal cusps posterodistally with one small cusp, not multiple; maxilliped, palp segment 2 linear, inner margin densely setose; dactylus of pereopods 3–7 medium in length (
<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFCCFF54277FF905FD73F95D" author="Labay, V. S." box="[626,766,1721,1747]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" pagination="220 - 230" refId="ref6589" refString="Labay, V. S. (2018) Cognateosymtes serraticoxae, new genus, new species, a pleustid amphipod from the Sea of Japan (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Gammaridea: Pleustidae: Eosymtinae). Zootax a, 4521 (2), 220 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4521.2.4" type="journal article" year="2018">Labay 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CBB6542FFCCFF5425CAF961FADDF8B1" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFCCFF5425CAF961FADDF8B1" blockId="2.[151,1437,1217,1856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF5425CAF961FEB6F979" bold="true" box="[199,315,1757,1783]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFCCFF542449F961FE50F979" author="Labay, V. S." box="[324,477,1757,1783]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" pagination="220 - 230" refId="ref6589" refString="Labay, V. S. (2018) Cognateosymtes serraticoxae, new genus, new species, a pleustid amphipod from the Sea of Japan (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Gammaridea: Pleustidae: Eosymtinae). Zootax a, 4521 (2), 220 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4521.2.4" type="journal article" year="2018">Labay (2018)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out as one of the signs the setulation of outer and inner plates of maxilla 2: “ 
<taxonomicName id="93A14D4AFFCCFF5425A9F8BEFED1F892" authorityName="Labay" authorityYear="2018" box="[164,348,1794,1820]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pleustidae" genus="Cognateosymtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF5425A9F8BEFED1F892" box="[164,348,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Cognateosymtes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="93A14D4AFFCCFF5424E3F8BEFDD5F895" authorityName="Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks" authorityYear="1994" box="[494,600,1794,1819]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pleustidae" genus="Eosymtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF5424E3F8BEFDD5F895" box="[494,600,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Eosymtes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by … outer and inner plates of maxilla 2 with numerous apical setae”. The following description of the new species 
<taxonomicName id="93A14D4AFFCCFF542769F89AFCFAF8B1" authority="Labay, 2022" authorityName="Labay" authorityYear="2022" box="[612,887,1829,1855]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pleustidae" genus="Eosymtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnumoculis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF542769F89AFCFAF8B1" box="[612,887,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">Eosymtes magnumoculis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFCCFF542672F899FC55F8B1" bold="true" box="[895,984,1829,1855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7DE657A0FFCCFF542672F899FC55F8B1" box="[895,984,1829,1855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="549" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
shows that this feature is invalid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
